[normal]Appendix A[bold]: Summary of Activities against the Police and Crime Plan Strategic Priority Themes[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Theme: Priority 1:[bold]Protect, support and respond to victims, witnesses and vulnerable people[bold]What we have been doing[bold]?[bold]Status[bold](RAG)[bold]Commissioners’ Activities[bold]PCP C1.1 Develop a Victims’ Strategy and Commissioning Framework based upon evidence of need
[normal].
[normal]The Commissioner is seeking support from the MOJ to start commissioning locally from October 2014. 
[normal]There has been a Project Initiation Document produced to outline the delivery of the Commissioner's Victim's Strategy. There
[normal] has also been ongoing work to develop
[normal] the Commissioning Framework as part of the Commissioner's Accountability Cycle
[normal] which will be delivered before April 2014 in line with refreshing the Police and Crime Plan
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]The Nottinghamshire Victim Support Annual Review highlighted the continued support that the Force provides in helping victims of 
[normal]crime;
[normal] there is a new Valuing Victims Intranet site for officers and staff to drive improved victim care and satisfaction.
[normal]A[bold]PCP C1.2 Work with ‘Victim Support’ to secure funding for Anti-Social Behaviour Case Workers.
[normal]Following discussions with District Councils and Partners it was identified that there was no gap in funding for 2013/14. The future funding of Case Workers will be reviewed as part of the Victims' Strategy and Commissioning Framework.
[normal]G[bold]PCP C1.3 Improve support to young victims of crime. 
[normal]There has been 
[normal]ongoing 
[normal]work 
[normal]with Community Safety partners to review the
[normal] needs of young victims 
[normal]which 
[normal]has been assessed and will form part of the Victims' Strategy.
[normal] 
[normal]There is development work with 16-18 year olds experiencing domestic abuse through grant funding, together with further support for child victims of domestic abuse.
[normal] Community Safety Partnership commissioning of Victim Support Work and SAFE
[normal] Scheme for victims, and improving healthy relationships such as the Vibe project.
[normal]A[bold]PCP C1.4 Through a better understanding, protect and reduce violence to young women and girls in gangs.
[normal]Work has been continuing with the Deputy PCC, 
[normal]Health Shop
[normal] commissioned 
